body:
@jdeppe-pivotal yes, the goal is to fix this in all applicable places but I've tried to minimize the impact by pulling on one thread starting with `MemberConfigManager.java` as that class was my introduction to the issue. 

The intention is to tackle this with several pull requests against `GEODE-6588` until the issue is fully addressed. 

The alternative is to turn this into a bigger pull request which applies the changes to all applicable classes in the `execute` packages which will take more time to accomplish.

> @albertogpz Thanks for working on the Geode and submitting this PR. Please address the review comments.
> I had started working on this; I thought I had updated the assignee on this ticket, but looks like I missed it. I also have additional changes which collapses execute/reexecute methods to one function. Once you push this changes, I can add that over this.
> Also, the ticket mentions about other function execution semantics (onServer, onServers), If you haven't worked on this, I have changes (work in-progress) for it and can add after your changes are merged.

@agingade Sorry if I stepped over some work you had already started. I did not work on the onServer and onServers refactoring so I will leave that to you if you have already some changes in progress.
I will address the review comments and then you can build on top of them.

@albertogpz No issues. Please go ahead and commit your changes after addressing the review comments. Don't close the ticket. I will add my changes on top of this.
